==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Great [[Britain]]'''

#The island (and some of the surrounding smaller islands) off the north-west coast of Europe made up of the countries [[England]], [[Scotland]] and [[Wales]].  Abbreviation: [[GB]].
#(''formerly, or loosely'') the [[UK]].

====Usage notes====
In older writing the phrase 'Great Britain' is often used to mean the [[United Kingdom]]. Today it is rarely used in English except as a purely geographical term. In most contexts it is replaced by [[Britain]]. 

